    (Wiebe et al., 2005).
    A general covering term for such states is private state, &#8220;a state that is not open to objective observation or verification&#8221; (Quirk et al., 1985).1 There are three main types of subjective expressions:2 His alarm grew.
    He absorbed the information quickly.
    He was boiling with anger.
    (2) references to speech (or writing) events expressing private states: UCC/Disciples leaders roundly condemned the Iranian President&#8217;s verbal assault on Israel.
    The editors of the left-leaning paper attacked the new House Speaker.
    He would be quite a catch.
    What&#8217;s the catch?
    That doctor is a quack.
    Work on automatic subjectivity analysis falls into three main areas.
